The PLR-22 pistol is chambered for the popular and economical .22 Long Rifle cartridge (.22LR). It is based on the 5.56mm NATO chambered PLR-16 pistol and shares many parts including the grip and front and rear sights. The PLR-22 is not a simple conversion kit, it is a standalone firearm chambered for the .22LR and is designed for target shooting, plinking, or small game hunting. The PLR-22 operates by blowback action and has a 4140 steel bolt that rides on steel guide rails inside the polymer receiver. The ejector is attached to one of the guide rails and the recoil spring is located above the barrel. The cross-bolt safety and magazine release operate identically to the PLR-16 and SU-16.

title: For Sale:  Beeman P3 Air Pistol by Weirauch - Free Shipping
postcontent:
I bought this from Pyramid Air about 2 years ago.  I might have fired it 100 times or so in my garage to train my wrists and elbows for indoor bullseye competition while .22LR ammo was in such short supply.  It turns out that I don't have the time for this sort of activity anyway, so I'm offering this incredible air pistol for sale.

If you're reading this far, I don't have to elaborate the difference between the German P3 and the Chinese-made P17.  They look the same, but they're completely different animals and I leave it at that.  Pyramid did a video on the P3 where they'd gauged the trigger at 1.2 pounds and chronographed the pistol at velocities upward of 370 fps. Noise maxed out at around 95 db, so it's fine for basement or garage use with a proper pellet trap.  The accuracy is exceptional.  The right person could easily compete with it in 10-meter matches alongside pistols that cost several times as much.

I'm sending the remaining can of Crossman .177 air pellets (this pistol will not shoot bb's), an open pack of NRA 5-meter targets, and an Allen pistol rug.  Below is a list of US states and/or municipalities that Pyramid will not ship to due to state/local laws regarding the shipment of air guns.  For that reason, I can not ship to mailing addresses within those areas.  The responsibility rests with the buyer for knowing their own local and state statutes. Thank you for looking!
